            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25456",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "see ZF-3490 : For the memcached backend, there is a lifetime limit of 30 days (2592000 seconds)\n\nso we should transform null to 2592000 (instead of 0), shouldn't we ?\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-10-27T12:00:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-10-27T12:00:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25745",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mauricio",
                        "name": "mauricio",
                        "displayName": "Mauricio Cuenca",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think you should stay with null to 0. This is value expected by PHP's Memcache module.\n\nMaybe the people from Memcached ships a new version supporting a longer lifetime, this way, passing 0 will guarantee the max allowed lifetime without changing the code.\n",
